        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 1 at 2:42PM PDT until July 1 at 3:30PM PDT by NWS Las Vegas NV</headline>
        <description>SVRVEF

The National Weather Service in Las Vegas has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
West central Clark County in southern Nevada...

* Until 330 PM PDT.

* At 242 PM PDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Sandy Valley,
or 12 miles southwest of Blue Diamond, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Jean, Blue Diamond, Sandy Valley, Goodsprings, Mountain Springs,
Spring Mountain Ranch, and Mt. Potosi.

This includes Interstate 15 in Nevada between mile markers 1 and 14.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
